// Numbers are in a *metabolic* watt frame (running energetics), so CP here is a
// metabolic ceiling — larger than the mechanical W/kg read off a cycling power
// meter. They're calibrated so an elite outlier (stamina 10, ~75 kg) carries a
// ~45 kJ reserve, a flat-out sprint nets ~1.5 kW above CP (≈⅓ of the tank per
// 10 s), and a walk refills it in ~1–2 min — matching modern GPS match data.
